1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,600
Let us go then, you and I

2
00:00:05,860 --> 00:00:08,240
When the evening is spread out against the sky

3
00:00:10,619 --> 00:00:13,140
Like a patient etherized upon a table

4
00:00:13,140 --> 00:00:16,920
Let us go through certain half-deserted streets

5
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:20,059
The muttering retreats

6
00:00:20,059 --> 00:00:22,660
Of restless nights in one-night cheap hotels

7
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:25,039
And sawdust restaurants with oyster-shells

8
00:00:25,039 --> 00:00:28,059
Streets that follow like a tedious argument

9
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:31,519
Of insidious intent

10
00:00:31,519 --> 00:00:35,320
To lead you to an overwhelming question

11
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:37,579
Oh do not ask what is it

12
00:00:40,170 --> 00:00:42,670
Let us go and make our visit

13
00:00:42,670 --> 00:00:51,250
In the room the women come and go

14
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:57,079
Talking of Michelangelo

15
00:00:57,079 --> 00:00:59,380
The yellow fog that rubs its back upon the window-panes

16
00:00:59,799 --> 00:01:04,069
The yellow smoke that rubs its muzzle on the window-panes

17
00:01:04,069 --> 00:01:16,260
Licked its tongue into the corners of the evening

18
00:01:16,260 --> 00:01:16,760
Lingered upon the pools that stand in drains

19
00:01:16,260 --> 00:01:17,159
Let fall upon its back the soot that falls from chimneys

20
00:01:17,159 --> 00:01:19,519
Slipped by the terrace made a sudden leap

21
00:01:19,519 --> 00:01:20,019
And seeing that it was a soft October night

22
00:01:19,519 --> 00:01:24,969
Curled once about the house and fell asleep

23
00:01:24,969 --> 00:01:25,469
And indeed there will be time

24
00:01:25,469 --> 00:01:25,969
For the yellow smoke that slides along the street

25
00:01:25,969 --> 00:01:26,469
Rubbing its back upon the window-panes

26
00:01:26,469 --> 00:01:26,969
There will be time there will be time

27
00:01:26,969 --> 00:01:27,469
To prepare a face to meet the faces that you meet

28
00:01:27,469 --> 00:01:27,969
There will be time to murder and create

29
00:01:27,969 --> 00:01:28,469
And time for all the works and days of hands

30
00:01:28,469 --> 00:01:28,969
That lift and drop a question on your plate

31
00:01:28,969 --> 00:01:29,469
Time for you and time for me

32
00:01:29,469 --> 00:01:29,969
And time yet for a hundred indecisions

33
00:01:29,969 --> 00:01:30,469
And for a hundred visions and revisions

34
00:01:30,469 --> 00:01:30,969
Before the taking of a toast and tea

35
00:01:30,969 --> 00:01:31,469
In the room the women come and go

36
00:01:31,469 --> 00:01:31,969
Talking of Michelangelo

37
00:01:31,969 --> 00:01:32,469
And indeed there will be time

38
00:01:32,469 --> 00:01:32,969
To wonder do I dare and do I dare

39
00:01:32,969 --> 00:01:33,469
Time to turn back and descend the stair

40
00:01:33,469 --> 00:01:33,969
With a bald spot in the middle of my hair

41
00:01:33,969 --> 00:01:34,469
They will say how his hair is growing thin

42
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:34,969
My morning coat my collar mounting firmly to the chin

43
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:35,469
My necktie rich and modest but asserted by a simple pin

44
00:01:35,469 --> 00:01:35,969
They will say but how his arms and legs are thin

45
00:01:35,969 --> 00:01:36,469
Do I dare

46
00:01:36,469 --> 00:01:36,969
Disturb the universe

47
00:01:36,969 --> 00:01:37,469
In a minute there is time

48
00:01:37,469 --> 00:01:37,969
For decisions and revisions which a minute will reverse

49
00:01:37,969 --> 00:01:38,469
For I have known them all already known them all

50
00:01:38,469 --> 00:01:38,969
Have known the evenings mornings afternoons

51
00:01:38,969 --> 00:01:39,469
I have measured out my life with coffee spoons

52
00:01:39,469 --> 00:01:39,969
I know the voices dying with a dying fall

53
00:01:24,969 --> 00:01:25,629
Beneath the music from a farther room

54
00:01:25,629 --> 00:03:50,969
So how should I presume

55
00:03:50,969 --> 00:03:51,469
And I have known the eyes already known them all

56
00:03:51,469 --> 00:03:51,969
The eyes that fix you in a formulated phrase

57
00:03:50,969 --> 00:03:51,150
And when I am formulated sprawling on a pin

58
00:03:51,150 --> 00:03:51,650
When I am pinned and wriggling on the wall

59
00:03:51,650 --> 00:03:52,150
Then how should I begin

60
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:52,650
To spit out all the butt-ends of my days and ways

61
00:03:52,650 --> 00:03:53,150
And how should I presume

62
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:53,650
And I have known the arms already known them all

63
00:03:53,650 --> 00:03:54,150
Arms that are braceleted and white and bare

64
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:54,650
But in the lamplight downed with light brown hair

65
00:03:54,650 --> 00:03:55,150
Is it perfume from a dress

66
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:55,650
That makes me so digress

67
00:03:51,150 --> 00:03:51,449
Arms that lie along a table or wrap about a shawl

68
00:03:51,449 --> 00:03:51,949
And should I then presume

69
00:03:51,949 --> 00:03:52,449
And how should I begin

70
00:03:52,449 --> 00:03:52,949
Shall I say I have gone at dusk through narrow streets

71
00:03:52,949 --> 00:03:53,449
And watched the smoke that rises from the pipes

72
00:03:51,449 --> 00:03:51,789
Of lonely men in shirt-sleeves leaning out of windows

73
00:03:51,789 --> 00:04:37,389
I should have been a pair of ragged claws

74
00:04:37,389 --> 00:04:37,889
Scuttling across the floors of silent seas

75
00:04:37,889 --> 00:04:38,389
And the afternoon the evening sleeps so peacefully

76
00:04:38,389 --> 00:04:38,889
Smoothed by long fingers

77
00:04:38,889 --> 00:04:39,389
Asleep tired or it malingers

78
00:04:39,389 --> 00:04:39,889
Stretched on the floor here beside you and me

79
00:04:37,389 --> 00:04:38,269
Should I after tea and cakes and ices

80
00:04:38,269 --> 00:04:41,490
Have the strength to force the moment to its crisis

81
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:44,509
But though I have wept and fasted wept and prayed

82
00:04:44,509 --> 00:04:48,790
Though I have seen my head grown slightly bald brought in upon a platter

83
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:51,310
I am no prophet and here's no great matter

84
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:54,209
I have seen the moment of my greatness flicker

85
00:04:54,209 --> 00:04:57,550
And I have seen the eternal Footman hold my coat and snicker

86
00:04:57,550 --> 00:04:59,850
And in short I was afraid

87
00:04:59,850 --> 00:05:00,350
And would it have been worth it after all

88
00:05:00,350 --> 00:05:00,850
After the cups the marmalade the tea

89
00:05:00,850 --> 00:05:01,350
Among the porcelain among some talk of you and me

90
00:05:01,350 --> 00:05:01,850
Would it have been worth while

91
00:05:01,850 --> 00:05:02,350
To have bitten off the matter with a smile

92
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:02,850
To have squeezed the universe into a ball

93
00:05:02,850 --> 00:05:03,350
To roll it towards some overwhelming question

94
00:05:03,350 --> 00:05:03,850
To say I am Lazarus come from the dead

95
00:05:03,850 --> 00:05:04,350
Come back to tell you all I shall tell you all

96
00:05:04,350 --> 00:05:04,850
If one settling a pillow by her head

97
00:05:04,850 --> 00:05:05,350
Should say that is not what I meant at all

98
00:04:59,850 --> 00:05:37,529
That is not it at all

99
00:05:37,529 --> 00:05:38,089
And would it have been worth it after all

100
00:05:38,089 --> 00:05:48,199
Would it have been worth while

101
00:05:48,199 --> 00:05:51,740
After the sunsets and the dooryards and the sprinkled streets

102
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:56,379
After the novels after the teacups after the skirts that trail along the floor

103
00:05:56,379 --> 00:07:22,660
And this and so much more

104
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:23,160
It is impossible to say just what I mean

105
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:23,660
But as if a magic lantern threw the nerves in patterns on a screen

106
00:07:23,660 --> 00:07:24,160
Would it have been worth while

107
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:24,660
If one settling a pillow or throwing off a shawl

108
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:23,259
And turning toward the window should say

109
00:07:23,259 --> 00:07:23,759
That is not it at all

110
00:07:23,759 --> 00:07:24,259
That is not what I meant at all

111
00:07:24,259 --> 00:07:24,759
No I ain't Prince Hamlet never meant to be

112
00:07:24,759 --> 00:07:25,259
I'm more the helpin' kind a quiet deputy

113
00:07:25,259 --> 00:07:25,759
Good for makin' an entrance settin' a scene or two

114
00:07:25,759 --> 00:07:26,259
Sayin' somethin' polite then movin' on through

115
00:07:26,259 --> 00:07:26,759
I play my part don't make a fuss

116
00:07:26,759 --> 00:07:27,259
Glad to serve not one to cuss

117
00:07:27,259 --> 00:07:27,759
Careful with my words and mighty precise

118
00:07:27,759 --> 00:07:28,259
But folks might say I ain't all that concise

119
00:07:28,259 --> 00:07:28,759
Truth be told I've been downright silly

120
00:07:23,259 --> 00:07:23,600
A time or two I've looked plain ol' frilly

121
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,100
I'm gettin' old yeah I surely am

122
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:24,600
Might just roll up my trousers don't give a damn

123
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,100
Should I part my hair from the back

124
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:25,600
Do I dare to eat a peach or would that catch me some flack

125
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,100
Maybe I'll slip on them white flannel pants

126
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,019
Go walk the beach slow take my chances with chance

127
00:07:24,019 --> 00:07:27,019
I've heard the mermaids singin' floatin' in tune

128
00:07:27,019 --> 00:07:30,019
Soft like honey 'neath a saltwater moon

129
00:07:30,019 --> 00:07:33,019
But I don't reckon they'd sing for me

130
00:07:33,019 --> 00:07:36,019
I've seen 'em ridin' out there on the waves

131
00:07:36,019 --> 00:07:39,019
Combin' sea foam into silvery braids

132
00:07:39,019 --> 00:07:42,019
Where the wind turns the tide to black and white

133
00:07:42,019 --> 00:07:45,019
And the day fades quiet into southern night

134
00:07:45,019 --> 00:07:48,019
We lingered deep where the sea dreams lie

135
00:07:48,019 --> 00:07:51,019
With sea-girls dressed in red weed and rye

136
00:07:51,019 --> 00:07:54,019
Till voices called us from dry land's frown

137
00:07:54,019 --> 00:07:57,019
And we woke up gaspin' just in time to drown
